00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.535 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Previously on "Dance Moms"--

00:00:02.602 --> 00:00:04.204 line:5%,start
We have a new member of the team.

00:00:04.537 --> 00:00:07.340 line:5%,start
Asia will be joining
the Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:00:07.407 --> 00:00:10.176 line:5%,start
I do not think there is enough
competition among you.

00:00:10.243 --> 00:00:11.911 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Well, doesn't it make you
nervous at all

00:00:11.978 --> 00:00:15.115 line:5%,start
that last week Abby really
didn't want Kenzie to do the group,

00:00:15.181 --> 00:00:18.351 line:5%,start
and then this week she brings in someone
that's her age and gives her a solo?

00:00:18.418 --> 00:00:23.790 line:5%,start
The top Energy Junior Small Group
is entry 124-A,

00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:24.858 line:5%,start
"Machine Lines."

00:00:24.924 --> 00:00:27.127 line:5%,start
[cheering and applause]

00:00:27.193 --> 00:00:31.197 line:5%,start
ABBY: Do you think I've given up my whole
life to deal with that piece of crap?

00:00:31.264 --> 00:00:32.098 line:5%,start
No!

00:00:32.165 --> 00:00:34.034 line:5%,start
She is dirt under my feet!

00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:36.736 line:5%,start
ABBY (VOICEOVER):
Coming up on "Dance Moms"--

00:00:36.836 --> 00:00:38.471 line:5%,start
We're doing a patriotic number.

00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:40.573 line:5%,start
This is about the politics--

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:41.975 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Of dance.
- --of dance.

00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:43.009 line:5%,start
ABBY: Politics is life.

00:00:43.076 --> 00:00:44.310 line:5%,start
It is about who you know.

00:00:44.377 --> 00:00:47.380 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: Maddie and Chloe are competing
against each other at this competition.

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:49.949 line:5%,start
ABBY: Now you realize
you're up against Chloe.

00:00:50.016 --> 00:00:51.751 line:5%,start
I mean, Asia comes in from out of town--

00:00:51.818 --> 00:00:53.486 line:5%,start
what do I do with Asia--

00:00:53.553 --> 00:00:55.155 line:5%,start
right when Mackenzie is injured.

00:00:55.221 --> 00:00:57.524 line:5%,start
She doesn't want to
let Asia take her spot.

00:00:57.590 --> 00:01:00.060 line:5%,start
Kendall, you're chasing her!

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:01.327 line:5%,start
The kid is a brat!

00:01:01.394 --> 00:01:03.530 line:5%,start
There are brats in there,
and Kendall's not one of them!

00:01:03.596 --> 00:01:05.098 line:5%,start
HOLLY: I don't care what you
say or what you don't say,

00:01:05.165 --> 00:01:07.367 line:5%,start
so let's get that clear.

00:01:07.434 --> 00:01:10.503 line:5%,start
ABBY: Today you will be
voting on Maddie or Chloe.

00:01:11.504 --> 00:01:12.705 line:5%,start
May the best man win.

00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.340 line:95%,end
[theme music]

00:01:15.241 --> 00:01:16.176 line:95%,end
(SINGING) Get up!

00:01:16.776 --> 00:01:18.645 line:95%,end
Get on the floor!

00:01:18.711 --> 00:01:24.884 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls,
living on the dance floor.

00:01:25.218 --> 00:01:28.188 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:01:31.691 --> 00:01:34.027 line:95%,end
Well, look at you, the first one in.

00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:38.898 line:95%,end
Wow. I love that your child and you
are the first ones in the door.

00:01:39.332 --> 00:01:40.467 line:5%,start
JILL: I don't like Kristie Rae.

00:01:40.567 --> 00:01:42.902 line:5%,start
She's been here just
a short period of time,

00:01:42.969 --> 00:01:46.272 line:5%,start
and she's already positioning
herself to be Abby's favorite.

00:01:46.372 --> 00:01:47.774 line:95%,end
ABBY: Congratulations, Asia.

00:01:47.874 --> 00:01:51.611 line:95%,end
It was your first time competing
with the Abby Lee Dance Company,

00:01:51.678 --> 00:01:53.279 line:95%,end
and you were the big winner.

00:01:53.379 --> 00:01:55.949 line:95%,end
[applause]

00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:57.917 line:95%,end
All right.

00:01:57.984 --> 00:02:01.321 line:5%,start
Last week, Cathy got
the only perfect score given.

00:02:01.421 --> 00:02:02.989 line:5%,start
It was horrible.

00:02:03.089 --> 00:02:07.594 line:5%,start
How come four strangers
that don't dance together

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:11.331 line:95%,end
on a daily basis, that aren't
taught by the same teacher,

00:02:11.431 --> 00:02:14.834 line:95%,end
come together and tell the story
and connect with each other?

00:02:14.901 --> 00:02:17.470 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:02:22.609 --> 00:02:24.844 line:95%,end
You're all together every single day.

00:02:24.944 --> 00:02:27.147 line:95%,end
I didn't see that connection.

00:02:27.247 --> 00:02:29.349 line:95%,end
I don't think some of you want to be here.

00:02:29.449 --> 00:02:33.153 line:95%,end
And I certainly don't think
any of you work hard enough.

00:02:36.523 --> 00:02:37.790 line:95%,end
The pyramid today--

00:02:39.526 --> 00:02:40.360 line:95%,end
first,

00:02:41.494 --> 00:02:42.595 line:95%,end
Mackenzie.

00:02:43.062 --> 00:02:45.131 line:95%,end
Mackenzie, you're injured.

00:02:45.198 --> 00:02:46.733 line:95%,end
You didn't dance. You stayed home.

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:48.868 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Mackenzie hurt her foot.

00:02:48.968 --> 00:02:50.503 line:5%,start
She just has an overuse injury.

00:02:50.603 --> 00:02:51.771 line:5%,start
She just has to rest.

00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:52.772 line:95%,end
And next,

00:02:53.773 --> 00:02:54.807 line:95%,end
we have Brooke.

00:02:56.209 --> 00:02:58.211 line:95%,end
You are 15 years old.

00:02:58.311 --> 00:02:59.512 line:95%,end
We all make choices.

00:02:59.612 --> 00:03:02.482 line:95%,end
If you want to work hard,
you'll get better.

00:03:03.616 --> 00:03:05.952 line:95%,end
Next, Chloe.

00:03:07.220 --> 00:03:09.322 line:95%,end
Chloe, you were part of a trio.

00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:10.423 line:95%,end
That trio should have won.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:11.324 line:5%,start
[music playing]

00:03:11.391 --> 00:03:12.492 line:5%,start
It was second.

00:03:12.559 --> 00:03:14.127 line:5%,start
You fell out of the turns early.

00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:16.129 line:5%,start
You hit the floor before everybody else.

00:03:16.663 --> 00:03:19.065 line:5%,start
CHRISTI: I think the only way
that Chloe will ever make it to the top

00:03:19.132 --> 00:03:22.869 line:5%,start
of the pyramid again is if she
may be reincarnates as Anna Pavlova.

00:03:22.936 --> 00:03:23.803 line:95%,end
And next,

00:03:25.104 --> 00:03:26.439 line:95%,end
Kendall.

00:03:26.506 --> 00:03:29.409 line:95%,end
You were also part
of a trio that came in second.

00:03:30.843 --> 00:03:32.312 line:95%,end
And now,

00:03:32.378 --> 00:03:33.446 line:95%,end
Maddie.

00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:36.950 line:95%,end
Maddie, you were a part of the trio, too.

00:03:37.483 --> 00:03:38.585 line:95%,end
What went wrong?

00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:41.554 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Maddie's fourth
on the pyramid and Abby said,

00:03:41.654 --> 00:03:44.290 line:95%,end
you know, you were
part of the losing trio.

00:03:44.357 --> 00:03:45.992 line:95%,end
I thought they were fabulous.

00:03:47.026 --> 00:03:47.927 line:95%,end
Next,


00:03:49.095 --> 00:03:50.530 line:95%,end
Paige.

00:03:50.763 --> 00:03:53.066 line:5%,start
KELLY: I'm glad that Paige
is moving her way up the pyramid.

00:03:53.132 --> 00:03:56.336 line:5%,start
With me behaving myself
and not fighting with Abby,

00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:58.004 line:95%,end
it's paying off for my kids.

00:03:58.071 --> 00:04:00.773 line:95%,end
Paige, if I give you the responsibility

00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:02.208 line:95%,end
to be part of the group number,

00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:05.612 line:95%,end
then work harder.

00:04:06.579 --> 00:04:07.580 line:95%,end
And next

00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.049 line:95%,end
I have Nia.

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:12.652 line:95%,end
Nia, you've been flying under the radar.

00:04:13.019 --> 00:04:18.091 line:95%,end
You're here because you're
like Switzerland.

00:04:19.158 --> 00:04:20.793 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Being second on
the pyramid is a big deal.

00:04:20.893 --> 00:04:23.997 line:95%,end
And I think Abby stole Nia's joy
by saying she got it

00:04:24.063 --> 00:04:25.932 line:95%,end
by flying under the radar.

00:04:26.032 --> 00:04:28.301 line:95%,end
I mean, that's defeating.

00:04:28.701 --> 00:04:31.871 line:95%,end
And next, on top of the pyramid, is Asia.

00:04:32.138 --> 00:04:34.707 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:04:35.875 --> 00:04:38.044 line:95%,end
ABBY: Asia, you were our big winner.

00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:40.146 line:95%,end
This is a reflection of your score,

00:04:41.447 --> 00:04:43.716 line:95%,end
not your legs or your feet.

00:04:45.451 --> 00:04:49.455 line:95%,end
Those things all need a lot of attention.

00:04:50.723 --> 00:04:51.924 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:04:52.725 --> 00:04:56.229 line:5%,start
KRISTIE: This week, Asia brought it
and now we're on top of the pyramid.

00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:57.764 line:5%,start
Mackenzie, what's wrong?

00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:00.800 line:5%,start
ABBY: You feel dizzy?

00:05:00.867 --> 00:05:02.468 line:95%,end
All right.
Why don't you take a seat?

00:05:02.535 --> 00:05:03.736 line:95%,end
OK?

00:05:03.803 --> 00:05:05.138 line:95%,end
You want to keep that foot up.

00:05:06.506 --> 00:05:08.608 line:95%,end
Mackenzie has to stay off of her foot.

00:05:09.776 --> 00:05:11.244 line:95%,end
And you were her opposite,

00:05:12.178 --> 00:05:13.946 line:95%,end
and now you don't have an opposite.

00:05:14.013 --> 00:05:16.816 line:95%,end
So what do I do with Asia?

00:05:16.916 --> 00:05:20.520 line:95%,end
JILL: Asia and Mackenzie are so much
smaller than everybody else on this team,

00:05:20.586 --> 00:05:25.224 line:95%,end
that they both need to be in this group
number to offset one another.

00:05:25.291 --> 00:05:27.927 line:95%,end
They're both like two
cute little bookends.

00:05:28.361 --> 00:05:29.862 line:95%,end
ABBY: So you're going
to come into the group

00:05:29.929 --> 00:05:31.130 line:95%,end
and you're going to learn it.

00:05:31.197 --> 00:05:32.732 line:95%,end
But I don't know if you're in it or not.

00:05:32.799 --> 00:05:35.501 line:95%,end
KRISTIE: It's unfortunate
that Kenzie's hurt right now.

00:05:35.568 --> 00:05:38.471 line:95%,end
So I'm waiting patiently to see
if she's going to get a chance

00:05:38.538 --> 00:05:39.672 line:95%,end
to be in this group this week.

00:05:39.739 --> 00:05:41.674 line:95%,end
We're doing a patriotic number.

00:05:42.141 --> 00:05:45.144 line:95%,end
It's called "Free the People."

00:05:45.645 --> 00:05:48.848 line:95%,end
We have the conservatives
and the liberals.

00:05:48.948 --> 00:05:52.085 line:5%,start
Clearly, the Abby Lee Dance Company
is not a democracy.

00:05:52.151 --> 00:05:53.653 line:5%,start
Abby is a totalitarianist.

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:57.256 line:95%,end
Now, this week we're
going to Philadelphia.

00:05:57.323 --> 00:06:00.693 line:95%,end
We are attending
Powerhouse Dance Competition.

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:04.597 line:95%,end
After last weekend,
I need to put my best foot forward.

00:06:06.399 --> 00:06:09.369 line:95%,end
This whole fair thing,
with trying to spread it all around,

00:06:10.002 --> 00:06:11.003 line:95%,end
no.

00:06:11.471 --> 00:06:13.172 line:95%,end
Obviously, Asia,

00:06:13.573 --> 00:06:14.540 line:95%,end
you get another solo.

00:06:17.043 --> 00:06:20.980 line:95%,end
The name of your solo is "Ready for War."

00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:24.417 line:95%,end
So, Maddie, you have
another solo this week.

00:06:24.517 --> 00:06:28.187 line:95%,end
I think it's strange that Paige
is higher than Maddie on the pyramid,

00:06:28.254 --> 00:06:30.990 line:95%,end
but yet Maddie gets the solo
and Paige doesn't.

00:06:31.424 --> 00:06:35.128 line:95%,end
The name of your song is "I'm Trying."

00:06:36.596 --> 00:06:40.466 line:95%,end
Chloe, you will be doing a solo this week.

00:06:41.801 --> 00:06:45.204 line:95%,end
The name of your routine is
"Am I Here to Stay?"

00:06:46.472 --> 00:06:48.274 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Maddie and Chloe
are competing against each other.

00:06:48.341 --> 00:06:52.078 line:95%,end
And this is the first time in months
these two are going to go head-to-head.

00:06:52.178 --> 00:06:54.080 line:95%,end
JILL: Maddie is the consistent winner,

00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:56.716 line:95%,end
but I know Chloe is really hungry to win.

00:06:56.783 --> 00:06:59.819 line:95%,end
With their rivalry, anything could happen.

00:06:59.886 --> 00:07:01.954 line:95%,end
ABBY: All right.
Moms, you're dismissed.

00:07:02.021 --> 00:07:04.056 line:95%,end
Girls, spread apart. Let's warm up.

00:07:07.026 --> 00:07:08.361 line:95%,end
Go ahead.

00:07:08.461 --> 00:07:10.129 line:95%,end
Come here, girls.

00:07:10.196 --> 00:07:13.232 line:95%,end
So why did Mackenzie start crying, though,

00:07:13.299 --> 00:07:15.234 line:95%,end
all of a sudden, in the middle of pyramid?

00:07:15.301 --> 00:07:17.036 line:95%,end
Did you notice the timing?

00:07:19.705 --> 00:07:20.940 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Oh.

00:07:21.007 --> 00:07:23.776 line:95%,end
KELLY: Mackenzie started crying
as soon as Asia was announced

00:07:23.876 --> 00:07:25.578 line:95%,end
that she was at the top of the pyramid.

00:07:25.645 --> 00:07:26.612 line:95%,end
I think she's intimidated.

00:07:26.679 --> 00:07:28.815 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: It didn't even
register on my radar.

00:07:28.915 --> 00:07:31.617 line:95%,end
Melissa's daughters can't be out-danced.

00:07:31.717 --> 00:07:35.421 line:95%,end
So rather than have Asia
and Mackenzie go head-to-head,

00:07:35.488 --> 00:07:37.423 line:95%,end
Melissa pulls Kenzie from the dance.


00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:38.624 line:95%,end
Smart, Melissa.

00:07:38.724 --> 00:07:43.563 line:95%,end
ABBY: So this is loosely
based on the political system.

00:07:43.930 --> 00:07:45.798 line:95%,end
Every time we go to a dance competition

00:07:45.898 --> 00:07:48.468 line:95%,end
I hear people toss around the saying,

00:07:48.568 --> 00:07:49.969 line:95%,end
"Well, this is political.

00:07:50.036 --> 00:07:52.939 line:95%,end
Oh, well, she's going to win
because it's all politics,

00:07:53.473 --> 00:07:55.408 line:95%,end
that it's maybe me who you know."

00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:58.211 line:95%,end
Well, then I guess politics is life.

00:07:59.245 --> 00:08:01.013 line:95%,end
Because it is about who you know.

00:08:01.814 --> 00:08:04.016 line:95%,end
Hey, whatever it takes. Right?

00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:05.451 line:95%,end
[laughter]

00:08:05.518 --> 00:08:07.086 line:95%,end
- That's what this is about.
- That is true.

00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:08.855 line:95%,end
This is about politics--

00:08:08.955 --> 00:08:10.756 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Of dance.
--of dance.

00:08:10.823 --> 00:08:13.125 line:95%,end
The ALDC is very political.

00:08:13.192 --> 00:08:16.762 line:95%,end
We are all campaigning all the time
to keep our daughters on top.

00:08:17.396 --> 00:08:20.366 line:95%,end
(SINGING) I can feel it--

00:08:20.466 --> 00:08:23.669 line:95%,end
ABBY: This week we're who a routine called
"Free the People."

00:08:23.769 --> 00:08:28.174 line:95%,end
It's a big patriotic number,
and I think it's important for kids today

00:08:28.241 --> 00:08:30.510 line:95%,end
to realize that they have a voice.

00:08:31.477 --> 00:08:33.246 line:95%,end
Asia, pay attention to what they're doing.

00:08:33.980 --> 00:08:35.748 line:95%,end
Yes? I just gave you that one step
to work on,

00:08:35.815 --> 00:08:37.350 line:95%,end
but you need to pay attention
to this group.

00:08:37.416 --> 00:08:39.952 line:95%,end
Originally, this routine had four girls

00:08:40.019 --> 00:08:44.290 line:95%,end
on the conservative side
and four girls on the liberal side.

00:08:44.357 --> 00:08:46.125 line:95%,end
And with that, I'm going to let you go.

00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:49.195 line:95%,end
But with Mackenzie out on injured reserve,

00:08:49.295 --> 00:08:51.230 line:95%,end
I don't know what to do with Asia.

00:08:51.297 --> 00:08:53.866 line:95%,end
So I put Asia to work on her solo.

00:08:54.333 --> 00:08:56.702 line:95%,end
Rosie the Riveter. Say that.

00:08:56.802 --> 00:08:57.870 line:95%,end
Rosie the Riveter.

00:08:57.970 --> 00:08:59.572 line:95%,end
Do you know who that is?

00:08:59.639 --> 00:09:01.374 line:95%,end
Yeah. She's going to be Rosie the Riveter.

00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:02.575 line:95%,end
Rosa what?

00:09:02.642 --> 00:09:03.676 line:95%,end
Rosie the Riveter.

00:09:03.743 --> 00:09:06.445 line:95%,end
You know, the girl from war war ads.

00:09:06.913 --> 00:09:08.514 line:95%,end
So you need to be strong.

00:09:08.581 --> 00:09:09.649 line:95%,end
Give me the arm.

00:09:10.316 --> 00:09:12.318 line:95%,end
Woo! Look at that.

00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:15.488 line:95%,end
Asia is doing a hot, sassy, jazz routine

00:09:15.555 --> 00:09:18.457 line:95%,end
it's called "Ready for War,"
and it's based on the character

00:09:18.524 --> 00:09:19.358 line:95%,end
Rosie the Riveter.

00:09:19.425 --> 00:09:20.426 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:09:20.493 --> 00:09:21.928 line:95%,end
Five, six,

00:09:22.762 --> 00:09:24.063 line:95%,end
seven, eight.

00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:28.701 line:95%,end
Just keep it--
head and head and head and head.

00:09:28.768 --> 00:09:32.572 line:95%,end
Yes. I think Asia,
she could have been Rosie the Riveter.

00:09:32.638 --> 00:09:35.041 line:95%,end
She is one tough cookie.

00:09:35.107 --> 00:09:36.175 line:95%,end
All right, you're finished.

00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:37.443 line:95%,end
I'm going to let you go, Rosie.

00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:38.945 line:95%,end
Send in your co-worker.

00:09:42.048 --> 00:09:43.416 line:95%,end
OK, Chloe.

00:09:43.816 --> 00:09:47.520 line:95%,end
Chloe, the name
of this is "Am I Here to Stay?"

00:09:47.587 --> 00:09:49.789 line:95%,end
I mean, really, are you here to stay?

00:09:49.889 --> 00:09:52.558 line:95%,end
Are you going to come out
an amazing dancer?

00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:54.093 line:95%,end
Time will tell.

00:09:54.193 --> 00:09:56.462 line:95%,end
Chloe is holding a national title.

00:09:56.562 --> 00:09:59.298 line:95%,end
She needs to dig down deep to beat Maddie.

00:09:59.398 --> 00:10:00.366 line:95%,end
[music playing]

00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:04.270 line:95%,end
(MUSIC PLAYING) Every time
I think about the day you left me here,

00:10:04.337 --> 00:10:06.639 line:95%,end
I feel so cold inside.

00:10:06.706 --> 00:10:08.040 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Chloe is the underdog.

00:10:08.107 --> 00:10:11.077 line:95%,end
Abby plays favorites,
and Chloe is certainly not one of them.

00:10:11.143 --> 00:10:12.678 line:95%,end
OK, Chloe, that's all we're going to do.

00:10:12.745 --> 00:10:14.547 line:95%,end
And, like, let that really hang.

00:10:16.082 --> 00:10:17.917 line:95%,end
And then you can get straight again.

00:10:20.453 --> 00:10:21.587 line:95%,end
Nice. Better.

