The routine is a big hot mess right now.

00:13:52.431 --> 00:13:54.366 line:95%,end
But once I get Asia in this number,

00:13:54.433 --> 00:13:55.968 line:95%,end
I think it's going to come together.

00:13:56.035 --> 00:13:58.470 line:95%,end
We're going to start
the dance where we left off.

00:13:58.537 --> 00:14:01.106 line:95%,end
I figured out what I'm
going to do with you, Asia.

00:14:01.173 --> 00:14:04.310 line:95%,end
I don't like to throw kids
out in the end of the numbers,

00:14:04.376 --> 00:14:08.047 line:95%,end
but I think this will be inspirational.

00:14:08.147 --> 00:14:09.882 line:95%,end
I think the audience will love it.

00:14:09.982 --> 00:14:15.955 line:95%,end
And I am going to have you come running
onto the stage with the American flag.

00:14:16.021 --> 00:14:18.824 line:95%,end
I want to use Asia
in this patriotic number

00:14:18.891 --> 00:14:20.826 line:95%,end
because she's a little firecracker.

00:14:20.893 --> 00:14:23.295 line:95%,end
So I decided to let Asia carry the flag.

00:14:23.362 --> 00:14:24.797 line:95%,end
Now, this is very important.

00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:27.199 line:95%,end
A flag it's never supposed
to touch the ground.

00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:30.002 line:95%,end
You need to be careful
that it never touches the ground.

00:14:30.069 --> 00:14:35.007 line:95%,end
I met with a tutor today, you know,
just asking questions about homeschooling.


00:14:35.074 --> 00:14:36.242 line:95%,end
JILL: Oh, you did?

00:14:36.342 --> 00:14:37.843 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Mm-hmm.
JILL: What's your next step?

00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:39.378 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I don't know if I'm doing it yet.
JILL: You find a tutor--

00:14:39.445 --> 00:14:40.846 line:95%,end
I still don't know if I'm doing it yet.

00:14:40.913 --> 00:14:43.082 line:95%,end
Do you want them to get more dance class?

00:14:43.148 --> 00:14:44.550 line:95%,end
Totally.

00:14:44.617 --> 00:14:47.453 line:5%,start
KELLY: I think the only reason
Melissa's pulling her kids out of school

00:14:47.519 --> 00:14:50.055 line:5%,start
is to get them ahead in the dance world.

00:14:50.155 --> 00:14:52.024 line:95%,end
And that's a crock of [bleep].

00:14:52.091 --> 00:14:53.425 line:95%,end
I'm definitely going to do it next year.

00:14:53.525 --> 00:14:56.695 line:95%,end
I mean, it's a definite for next year,
no question.

00:14:56.762 --> 00:14:59.098 line:95%,end
Maddie and Mackenzie want to homeschool.

00:14:59.164 --> 00:15:00.165 line:95%,end
They want more time.

00:15:00.232 --> 00:15:01.867 line:95%,end
They can dance more.

00:15:01.934 --> 00:15:04.870 line:95%,end
They'll be able to sleep
another hour in the morning.

00:15:04.937 --> 00:15:10.009 line:95%,end
What do you want out of this experience
that the school can't provide you?

00:15:10.075 --> 00:15:11.510 line:95%,end
Mackenzie's going to take piano.

00:15:11.577 --> 00:15:14.847 line:95%,end
Like-- like, it'll be fun for her to take
a piano class. You know?

00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:16.181 line:95%,end
Like, I might take piano.

00:15:16.248 --> 00:15:17.516 line:5%,start
I know Melissa will do anything

00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:19.785 line:5%,start
to make sure that her
daughters are the best dancers.

00:15:19.885 --> 00:15:22.421 line:95%,end
But taking your kids out of school
is really serious,

00:15:22.488 --> 00:15:25.457 line:95%,end
and I'm not sure that Melissa is
doing it for the right reasons.

00:15:25.524 --> 00:15:27.493 line:95%,end
School is not just about busy work.

00:15:27.559 --> 00:15:30.095 line:95%,end
It's about can you think.

00:15:30.195 --> 00:15:33.265 line:95%,end
Can you be a citizen of the world
and think for yourself?

00:15:33.365 --> 00:15:34.833 line:95%,end
I just really agree with Holly.

00:15:34.900 --> 00:15:35.868 line:95%,end
I really do.

00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:39.071 line:5%,start
Isn't our role as a parent to make sure
our children grow up educated?

00:15:39.138 --> 00:15:41.273 line:5%,start
The only thing Maddie's
going to know is a tendu!

00:15:41.373 --> 00:15:44.710 line:95%,end
These are hard questions because your child
gets one chance at education.

00:15:46.612 --> 00:15:47.947 line:95%,end
Run again for me. Run.

